## 5. Experimental Data & Parameter Extraction

To ground the mathematical model in reality, parameters were extracted from experimental data provided from a research paper on VOx memristors. 

### Critical Discovery: Biasing Mode
Analysis of the paper's axes revealed that the majority of the data (Figures 3, 4, and 5) were **Current-Biased** measurements. This required the expansion of the codebase to support Current-Bias ODEs (Layer 5b), as the physics of Joule heating shift dramatically from $V^2/R$ (which causes thermal runaway as $R$ drops) to $I^2 R$ (which is self-limiting and stable as $R$ drops).

### Extracted Parameters
Visual analysis of the R-T and V-I curves yielded the following calibration parameters for the model:

| Parameter | Extracted Value | Physical Meaning | Source Figure |
| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |
| **$R_{insulating}$** | $25,000\,\Omega$ | Resistance of pure monoclinic phase | Fig 2 (R-T curve, lower T) |
| **$R_{metallic}$** | $100\,\Omega$ | Resistance of pure rutile phase | Fig 2 (R-T curve, higher T) |
| **$T_{amb}$** | $295 - 297\,K$ | Ambient testing environment | Labeled on Figures 3, 5, 6 |
| **$T_{IMT}$** | $308\,K$ | Heating transition point | Fig 2 (steepest R drop) |
| **$T_{MIT}$** | $302\,K$ | Cooling transition point | Fig 2 (steepest R rise) |
| **$\Delta T$** | $4.0\,K$ | Sharpness of transition | Fig 2 (width of R drop) |
| **$G_{th}$** | $5.0 \times 10^{-5}\,W/K$ | Substrate heat dissipation rate | Derived from Fig 5 switching power |
| **$C_{th}$** | $1.0 \times 10^{-9}\,J/K$ | Effective thermal mass | Standard for thin films |

