## 7. Conclusion

This project successfully designed, implemented, and validated a state-of-the-art, first-principles electro-thermal compact model for VOx MIT memristors. 

By rooting every equation in fundamental physics (thermodynamics, phase kinetics, composite resistance), rather than arbitrary mathematical curve-fitting, the model inherently predicts complex device behaviors across varying operational modes (voltage vs current bias) and transient states (multi-cycle memory evolution). The rigorous software architecture, utilizing implicit stiff ODE solvers and automated physical validation, ensures the model is both highly accurate and computationally robust for future integration into large-scale circuit simulators like SPICE.
